Definition ltof (a b:A) := f a < f b.
Definition gtof (a b:A) := f b > f a.
assert (H : forall n (a:A), f a < n -> Acc ltof a).
intros; absurd (f a < 0); auto with arith.
apply Nat.lt_le_trans with (f a); auto with arith.
Theorem induction_ltof1 : forall P:A -> Set, (forall x:A, (forall y:A, ltof y x -> P y) -> P x) -> forall a:A, P a.
assert (H : forall n (a:A), f a < n -> P a).
intros; absurd (f a < 0); auto with arith.
apply Nat.lt_le_trans with (f a); auto with arith.
Theorem induction_gtof1 : forall P:A -> Set, (forall x:A, (forall y:A, gtof y x -> P y) -> P x) -> forall a:A, P a.
Theorem induction_ltof2 : forall P:A -> Set, (forall x:A, (forall y:A, ltof y x -> P y) -> P x) -> forall a:A, P a.
Theorem induction_gtof2 : forall P:A -> Set, (forall x:A, (forall y:A, gtof y x -> P y) -> P x) -> forall a:A, P a.
Hypothesis H_compat : forall x y:A, R x y -> f x < f y.
assert (H : forall n (a:A), f a < n -> Acc R a).
intros; absurd (f a < 0); auto with arith.

Lemma lt_wf_rec1 : forall n (P:nat -> Set), (forall n, (forall m, m < n -> P m) -> P n) -> P n.
exact (fun p P F => induction_ltof1 nat (fun m => m) P F p).
Lemma lt_wf_rec : forall n (P:nat -> Set), (forall n, (forall m, m < n -> P m) -> P n) -> P n.
exact (fun p P F => induction_ltof2 nat (fun m => m) P F p).
Lemma lt_wf_ind : forall n (P:nat -> Prop), (forall n, (forall m, m < n -> P m) -> P n) -> P n.
intro p; intros; elim (lt_wf p); auto with arith.
Lemma gt_wf_rec : forall n (P:nat -> Set), (forall n, (forall m, n > m -> P m) -> P n) -> P n.
Lemma gt_wf_ind : forall n (P:nat -> Prop), (forall n, (forall m, n > m -> P m) -> P n) -> P n.
Lemma lt_wf_double_rec : forall P:nat -> nat -> Set, (forall n m, (forall p q, p < n -> P p q) -> (forall p, p < m -> P n p) -> P n m) -> forall n m, P n m.
intros P Hrec p; pattern p; apply lt_wf_rec.
intros n H q; pattern q; apply lt_wf_rec; auto with arith.
Lemma lt_wf_double_ind : forall P:nat -> nat -> Prop, (forall n m, (forall p (q:nat), p < n -> P p q) -> (forall p, p < m -> P n p) -> P n m) -> forall n m, P n m.
intros P Hrec p; pattern p; apply lt_wf_ind.
intros n H q; pattern q; apply lt_wf_ind; auto with arith.
Definition inv_lt_rel x y := exists2 n, F x n & (forall m, F y m -> n < m).
Hypothesis F_compat : forall x y:A, R x y -> inv_lt_rel x y.
Remark acc_lt_rel : forall x:A, (exists n, F x n) -> Acc R x.
intros x [n fxn]; generalize dependent x.
Lemma well_founded_inv_rel_inv_lt_rel : forall (A:Set) (F:A -> nat -> Prop), well_founded (inv_lt_rel A F).
intros; apply (well_founded_inv_lt_rel_compat A (inv_lt_rel A F) F); trivial.
Definition has_unique_least_element (A:Type) (R:A->A->Prop) (P:A->Prop) := exists! x, P x /\ forall x', P x' -> R x x'.
Lemma dec_inh_nat_subset_has_unique_least_element : forall P:nat->Prop, (forall n, P n \/ ~ P n) -> (exists n, P n) -> has_unique_least_element le P.
assert (forall n, (exists n', n'<n /\ P n' /\ forall n'', P n'' -> n'<=n'') \/ (forall n', P n' -> n<=n')).
